Title: Object: A Caramanian family changing it's abode
Series: Views in Egypt, Palestine and other parts of the Ottoman Empire
Description: Plate 14 in volume III: a man with a turban, carrying a hand axe over his left shoulder, a load on his back, holding a stick with his right hand, walking to right, following a group of people, including a woman holding a baby on horseback; more people walking or riding horses in the right foreground; after Mayer; published state. 1803 Hand-coloured aquatint with etching
Bibliographic references: Abbey Travel / Travel in Aquatint and lithography 1770-1860 from the library of J.R.Abbey (369.III.14)
